<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Supports Peaceful Solution to Cyprus Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Egypt Backs a peaceful solution to
the Cyprus issue, which is based on the U.N. resolutions, Egyptian
Ambassador to Cyprus Omar Metwally said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Metwally told the Cyprus News Agency that Egypt is "looking
forward to the day when Cyprus will be reunited as one country with
one international personality."
</P>
<P>
The Cyprus solution, he said, should also be acceptable to both
the Greek Cypriots and Turkish Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has remained divided since 1974 when Turkish troops took
over the northern third of the island in reaction to a pro-Athens
coup in Nicosia.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations has been trying for decades to reunite the
island through a bizonal, bicommunal federation formula, but so far
no tangible results have been achieved.
</P>
<P>
Metwally described the relations between Egypt and Cyprus,
especially in the political field, as "excellent and close", adding
that they could be further boosted in the economic and the cultural
fields.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Metwally announced that an Egyptian Cultural Week and
Film Festival will be held in Nicosia on May 5-18, which will be
featured by movies, traditional folkloric dancing and contemporary
Egyptian art. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Continues Turkey Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said here Thursday that China would like to join hands with Turkey
to promote the bilateral relations on various levels.
</P>
<P>
China believes that fruitful results will be achieved in its
friendly cooperation with Turkey in the new century after the two
countries forged a new type of partnership, he said at a banquet
hosted by Governor of Istanbul Erol Gakir in his honor.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president arrived in this largest city of Turkey in
the morning from the Turkish capital of Ankara to continue his
state visit in the country.
</P>
<P>
At the banquet, Jiang termed Istanbul, which straddles the Asian
and European continents, as a city of charm and a golden bridge
linking the East and West.
</P>
<P>
He said that the economic progress and vitality of the city have
deeply impressed him.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also spoke highly of the role the city has played in the
Sino-Turkish friendship, noting that the ancient Silk Road extended
from then China's capital Xi'an to Istanbul.
</P>
<P>
Gakir extended his warm welcome to Jiang, saying that Jiang's
visit has written a new chapter in the history of the development
of the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
As a world-known historic and cultural city and an economic
center, Istanbul will play a significant role in furthering the
Turkey-China relations, Gakir added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, President Jiang toured an electronic
facility manufacturing company in the city. Together with his
Turkish counterpart Suleyman Demirel, Jiang also met with Turkish
businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Jiang arrived in Turkey Tuesday for a state visit as the guest
of Demirel. This is the third leg of his five-nation visit, which
had taken him to Israel and Palestine, and will take him to Greece
and South Africa.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
