<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0009 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton, Mori to Meet in May  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Japan's new Prime Minister
Yoshiro Mori will meet with President Bill Clinton on May 5 in
Washington to discuss bilateral relationship as well as issues for
July's G8 summit in Okinawa, the White House said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
White House spokesman Joe Lockhart said he understood that Mori,
who became Japan's leader after former Prime Minister Keizo Obuchi
was felled by a stroke earlier this month, tried to meet as many
of his G8 partners in advance of the Okinawa meeting.
</P>
<P>
"I expect in addition to our many important bilateral issues
that define our relationship, I expect there to be discussion of
the upcoming G8 meeting in Okinawa," he said.
</P>
<P>
The annual summit of G8, including Britain, Canada, France,
Germany, Italy, Japan, the United States and Russia, is scheduled
from July 21-23 on the southern island of Okinawa.
</P>
<P>
Japan's government spokesman Mikio Aoki said in Tokyo earlier
on Thursday that Mori wanted to visit the different countries to
build "close and personal trust" between them ahead of the Okinawa
summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
