<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nicaragua Exports Cheap, Qualified Labor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua has become a country
that exports cheap qualified labor to other nations, said Thursday
a Nicaraguan Non-Government Organizations (NGO) study.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that from 800,000 to 1.2 million Nicaraguan
have gone o Costa Rica and to the United States. A 43 percent of
the Nicaraguan women who are working as domestic laborers in Costa
Rica are teachers.
</P>
<P>
The emigration of Nicaraguan professionals to other countries
is a constant feature caused by the high indexes of poverty
existing in the country, says the NGO document.
</P>
<P>
A poll made by the Nicaraguan Research Institute between
February 24 and March 2 of this year shows that the living
standards deterioration of Nicaraguans has risen in the last years.
</P>
<P>
Eighty-eight percent of the Nicaraguan population lives in
poverty and lacks many basic services. These levels of poverty
force many Nicaraguans to seek between horizons, said the NGO
study.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0013 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Appeals for Specialized Units for Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The belligerent parties to the conflict in the DRC adopted the
plan on April 8 to disengage their forces from their current
confrontation lines.
</P>
<P>
In his latest report to the U.N. Security Council, Annan said
the U.N. Secretariat will continue actively to carry out the
logistical preparations for the deployment of the U.N. Mission in
the DRC (MONUC), mandated to monitor the cease-fire process there.
</P>
<P>
The mission would do everything it can to assist the parties to
finalize their disengagement plan, Annan said.
</P>
<P>
In February, the U.N. Security Council authorized the expansion
of the MONUC to 5,537 military personnel from the current 100
unarmed military liaison officers.
</P>
<P>
The MONUC also lacks some crucial units including airfield
crash rescue and firefighting, air traffic control, cargo handling
and water processing.
</P>
<P>
The humanitarian situation in the eastern DRC has deteriorated
rapidly since the beginning of this year, with some 550,000
internally displaced people caught up in the war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Holds Strategic Air Force Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Russia conducted an active stage
of tactical exercises of the national strategic air force Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Over 40 bombers and fighters, including Tu-160, Tu-95MC and Tu-
22MZ strategic bombers, Sukhoi-27 and MiG-29 fighters and an AN-50
radar reconnaissance plane, took part in the exercises, said the
Russian Air Force headquarters.
</P>
<P>
During Thursday's maneuver, Tu-22MZ bombers launched tactical
missiles in the area of the Black Sea. Cruise missiles were also
launched from Tu-160 and Tu-95MC bombers.
</P>
<P>
The missiles hit targets at a test ground in the middle reaches
of the Volga river.
</P>
<P>
The fighters and strategic aviation also conducted exercises in
interaction, the headquarters said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
