<HEADLINE> One Third of Ethiopian Cattle Population Die Every Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Some 34 percent of cattle
population in Ethiopia died of animal diseases annually though the
government exerted efforts to stem spread of animal diseases, Vice
Minister of Agriculture Belay Ejigu said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Belay told a workshop on animal disease control and vaccination
that the government has attached a paramount importance to
ensuring quarantine and surveillance system along with
strengthening the capacity of veterinary clinics and institutions
with a view to controlling and eventually eradicating animal
disease in general and rinderpest in particular from the country,
he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Belay, Ethiopia's National Veterinary Institute
has a capacity to produce 50 to 80 million doses of vaccines
annually for the prevention of various communicable and
non-communicable animal diseases. 
