<HEADLINE> New Oil Well Discovered in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- French oil company ELF Exploration
Angola has succeeded in sinking a new oil well in the offshore oil
field in Angola, the Angolan state oil company SONANGOL said here
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Named as "Jasmin-1", the newly found oil well is located some
200 kilometers from the Angolan capital Luanda, with an estimated
daily production of 10,800 barrels.
</P>
<P>
However, the two oil companies said, further geological and
engineering studies will be carried out to establish the real
capacity of the well.
</P>
<P>
The new well, drilled 1,392 meters deep, is the ninth
consecutive discovery in the Angolan deep water field block 17.
</P>
<P>
Other wells discovered on the block 17 are"Girassol", "Dalia",
"Rosa", " Lirio", "Tulipa","Orquidea", "Cravo" and "Camelia",
which are all named after flowers.
</P>
<P>
"ELF Exploration Angola" holds 35 percent of the block 17 while
the rest are shared by "ESSO Exploration Angola" ,"BP" "Statoil"
and other companies.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government divides its offshore waters into several
"blocks" for the exploration of oil. The foreign oil companies
have to bid against each other for the authority of the
exploration in the blocks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
