<HEADLINE> On-Line Chinese Newspapers Mushroom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 273 of Chinese newspapers
have created websites of their own, accounting for one seventh of
the country's total.
</P>
<P>
According to sources at the 21st China Internet Conference
which open today, about 116 Chinese newspapers have registered
their independent domain names, accounting for 42.6 percent of the
country's total. The rest have established their own homepages on
other websites.
</P>
<P>
Nearly one forth of the 273 newspapers are national ones and
about 213 regional and local newspapers have been providing on-
line services.
</P>
<P>
Most of the on-line provide morning and evening newspapers. On-
line economic newspapers come in second, totaling 41.
</P>
<P>
South China's Guangdong Province has most on-line newspapers in
China.  
</P>
