<HEADLINE> Chinese Tourism Makes A Mint In First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China reaped an income of 3.607
billion US dollars during the first quarter, up 17.72 percent over
the same period last year, said the State Tourism Administration
today.
</P>
<P>
During the three months, China received 19.1657 million
overseas tourists, up 15.52 percent. Of them, some 70.675 million
overseas tourists stayed for only one night, up 16.47 percent on a
yearly basis. These overseas tourists spent 3.281 billion US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists from Asia traveling in China saw the
highest growth rate in the world, at an annual rate of 25.79
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
