<HEADLINE> Today's Diplomatic News Highlights (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Following are the diplomatic news
highlights released by Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng Meets with Ukrainian Supreme Court Chairman
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress (NPC), met here today with Vitaly Boiko,
Ukrainian chairman of the Supreme Court, who arrived here
Wednesday for a week-long visit.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China and Ukraine have maintained friendly,
cooperative relations in various fields since the two countries
established diplomatic relations eight years ago. Boiko handed to
Li a letter from Ivan Plyushch, chairman of the Supreme Council of
Ukraine, who has invited Li to pay an official visit to Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
China-EU WTO Talks to Resume Soon
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi said here today
that Chinese trade minister Shi Guangsheng has again invited the
European Union (EU) delegation to come again to Beijing for a new
round of talks concerning China's entry to the World Trade
Organization (WTO).
</P>
<P>
So far, China has completed talks on its entry to the WTO with
more than 30 members of the organization.
</P>
<P>
Symposium on Confucius, Socrates Held
</P>
<P>
The second symposium on Confucius and Socrates, sponsored by
the Chinese Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries and
the Association for Development of Europe-China Relations of
Greece, was held here today.
</P>
<P>
Chinese, Gabonese FMs Held Talks
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan today held talks with
Gabonese State Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs,
Cooperation and French Countries Jean Ping in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Tang expressed satisfaction with the smooth growth of relations
of friendly cooperation between the two countries since they
forged diplomatic ties 26 years ago, and expressed appreciation
for the Gabonese government's adherence to the One China principle.
</P>
<P>
Ping spoke highly of China's achievements in social and
economic development, extended gratitude for China's selfless
assistance to Gabon's socio-economic growth, and reiterated that
Gabon will continue to develop friendly relations of cooperation
with China in all fields on the basis of the One China stance.
</P>
<P>
PLA Senior Officer Holds Talks with Australian Officer
</P>
<P>
Fu Quanyou, chief of the General Staff of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army (PLA), held talks here today with Christopher
Barrie, chief commander of the Australian defense forces.
</P>
<P>
Fu noted that the current international situation has changed
fundamentally, and multi-polarization is an irreversible trend.
While peace and development prevail in much of the world today,
hegemonism and power politics still exist, which bring instability,
he said.
</P>
