<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CAS Initiates Program for Young Talent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Sciences (
CAS) today started a program to introduce outstanding young
scientists in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The program will attract young Chinese scholars and experts who
have been studying or working overseas, said a CAS official.
</P>
<P>
People who are qualified for employment should be under 45
years old, and should have doctorate degrees and more than two
years of research work experience. They should have made
contributions that have been recognized worldwide or own patents
for major scientific inventions and innovations.
</P>
<P>
Those employed will receive two million yuan (about 241,000 US
dollars) in funds for research in the next three years, will be
well paid and be put up in good housing.
</P>
<P>
CAS announced the 348 research subjects including chemistry,
biology, mathematics, physics and computers.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the Chinese government decided to grant 600 million
yuan to help CAS invite 300 outstanding middle-aged and young
scientists from overseas to work at the Academy.
</P>
<P>
Prior to 1999, CAS had already attracted and supported 331
young scientists to work in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
