<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Exports Likely to Rise 10 Percent This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Thai exports to overseas markets
are expected to reach the government's target of 62 billion U.S.
dollars this year, an increase of 10 percent from last year, the
office of Thai Deputy Prime Minister and Commerce Minister
Supachai Panitchpakdi declared here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement from the office, the anticipated
growth of overall Thai exports this year was a fruitful result of
the government's continued policy to support expanded exports both
in key and new markets.
</P>
<P>
Thai exports in the first quarter of this year grew by 30
percent, particularly in the group of electrical appliances, and
are believed to grow at least 10 percent at the end of the year,
achieving the government's goal of 62 billion U.S. dollars, the
statement noted.
</P>
<P>
It said a recent survey also found that Thai products were most
recognized in the Southeast Asian markets, and Thailand had the
highest level of export values among Southeast Asian countries.
</P>
<P>
However, it said, that there would still be a need to
restructure the production process of Thai agricultural products
to be compliant with the international standard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
