<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macedonia Seizes Marijuana on Border With Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Macedonian customs authorities
have arrested a member of a major transnational drug ring in the
Balkans and seized 465 kilograms of highly refined marijuana at a
crossing on the country's border with Albania, the MIA news agency
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Police made the arrest late Tuesday night. The marijuana was in
468 bags and stashed in the cap of a truck waiting to enter
Macedonia, Stevo Pendarovski, a spokesman for Macedonia's Interior
Ministry was quoted as saying. The marijuana has a street value of
700,000 U.S. dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
The driver, who was arrested at the scene, is reportedly a
member of a major drug ring engaged in drug smuggling on the
Macedonia-Albania border, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The report said that since the early 1990s, Albania has become
a major producer of marijuana, and serves as a vital transit route
for drug dealers to smuggle drugs to the rest of Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
