<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Welcomes Shevardnadze's Re-Election as Georgian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) on
Thursday congratulated Eduard Shevardnadze on his re-election as
president of Georgia.
</P>
<P>
The EU hopes Shevardnadze's new term of office will contribute
to stability and the deepening of political, economical and
judicial reforms, with a view to establishing a democratic and
market-oriented society in Georgia, said a declaration of the EU.
</P>
<P>
The EU said it expects the re-election of Shevardnadze will
promote the partnership between the EU and Georgia.
</P>
<P>
However, the 15-nation bloc also regretted that the electoral
process in the former Soviet republic did not occur in accordance
with the commitments given by Georgia as a participating state of
the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) and
the Council of Europe.
</P>
<P>
"These elections stressed the need for Georgia to further the
reform of its electoral system in close cooperation with the OSCE,
" the EU declaration said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
