<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0078 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman on China's Poverty Relief Work (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), told a group of foreign guests that
eradicating poverty remains a tough task for China.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remarks in his meeting with delegates who are here
to attend an international symposium entitled "Glory Project
Marching Into The New Century". The symposium officially opens
tomorrow and runs until Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Glory Project is a poverty-relief charitable project sponsored
by China's private enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Li said that poverty is a problem among countries worldwide. "
China has vast territories, large population, and a backward
economy," he said, adding that living conditions are harsh in some
hilly, mountainous, remote and drought areas.
</P>
<P>
Eliminating poverty is a word-wide concern. "The Chinese
government places great importance on tackling the problem.
Particular after the reform and opening-up drive, China adopted a
series of effective measures," he said, adding that remarkable
results have been achieved.
</P>
<P>
Chinese people from all walks of life are taking part in
poverty relief work, he said. A number of poverty-relief projects,
including Glory Project, have emerged in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0079 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman on China's Poverty Relief Work (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Despite these efforts, poverty relief in China still faces
many difficulties and problems. We urged all friends present to
offer opinions and suggestions," he said.
</P>
<P>
Li described the poverty-relief work as "glorious, great and
lofty". He cited two Chinese idioms to elaborate his points. One
is "adding flowers to the brocade -- or making what is good still
better," and the other is "sending charcoal in snowy weather -- or
giving help for those in need." "The latter is more important and
valuable," he commented.
</P>
<P>
The Symposium will focus on eliminating poverty with the
combined efforts of the government, private enterprises and non-
governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
Officials, scholars and experts from China Glory Project
Promotion Council and several United Nations organizations will
attend the Symposium.
</P>
<P>
Wang Guangying, vice-chairman of the National People's Congress
Standing Committee, Wang Zhaoguo and Jing Shuping, two vice-
chairmen of CPPCC National Committee, were among those present at
today's meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
