<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bus Crash Kills 69 in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 20 (Xinhua) -- About 69 people were killed when
a bus collided head-on with a truck on Wednesday night, Kenya
police said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on the highway between the Kenyan capital
Nairobi and the Indian port city of Mombasa when people were
hurrying back to their hometown ahead of the Easter holiday,
according to police spokesman peter kimanthi.
</P>
<P>
This was the second serious road tragedy taking place in Kenya
within one month. O March 29, two buses collided in the western
part of the country, leaving more than 70 dead.
</P>
<P>
Poor road condition, over-loading and speeding have been blamed
for frequent accidents in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
