<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mbeki to Attend African Mini-Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Thabo Mbeki will join other African leaders in Zimbabwe for a
mini-summit on Friday, presidential aide Tasneem Carrim announced
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will probably take place in Victoria Falls, she
said.
</P>
<P>
Leaders expected to attend the meeting will also include
Southern African Development Community (SADC) Chairman and
Mozambican President Joaquim Chissano, SADC Deputy Chairman and
Namibian President Sam Nujoma, Chairman of the Organization of
African Unity and Algerian President Abdelaziz Bouteflika and
Nigerian President Olusegun Obasanjo.
</P>
<P>
The mini-summit had its roots in talks among African leaders
during the just-ended G-77 summit in Havana, Carrim said.
</P>
<P>
Problems in Angola and the Democratic Republic of the Congo are
among the issues to be discussed.
</P>
<P>
On whether the turmoil in Zimbabwe will be discussed, Carrim
said: "I don't see how they can meet and not discuss Zimbabwe, but
it is not the primary focus." 
</P>
</TEXT>
