<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Gabonese Foreign Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan today held talks with Gabonese State Minister and Minister
of Foreign Affairs, Cooperation and French Countries Jean Ping in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Tang expressed satisfaction with the smooth growth of relations
of friendly cooperation between the two countries since they
forged diplomatic ties 26 years ago, and expressed appreciation
for the Gabonese government's adherence to the One China principle.
</P>
<P>
China and Gabon are both developing countries that face common
tasks and challenges, Tang said. "We are willing to make concerted
efforts with Gabon to raise bilateral ties to a new level," he
added.
</P>
<P>
Ping spoke highly of China's achievements in social and
economic development, extended gratitude for China's selfless
assistance to Gabon's socio-economic growth, and reiterated that
Gabon will continue to develop friendly relations of cooperation
with China in all fields on the basis of the One China stance.
</P>
<P>
Ping also said Gabon will enhance its cooperation with China in
international affairs so as to safeguard the legitimate rights of
developing countries.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers exchanged views on the upcoming China-Africa
Cooperation Forum, a ministerial-level forum to be held in Beijing
next October.
</P>
<P>
Ping and his party arrived here earlier today for an official
visit at Tang's invitation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
