<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Chief of General Staff Holds Talks with Australian Guests (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, chief of the General
Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), held talks
here today with Christopher Barrie, chief commander of the
Australian defense forces.
</P>
<P>
Fu, also a member of the Central Military Commission, exchanged
views with Barrie on bilateral relations, regional and
international affairs and army building.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that China and Australia are important countries in
Asian-Pacific region, and the maintenance of the friendly
relations between the two countries conforms to the fundamental
interest of the people of China and Australia.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to continue cooperation and military exchanges
with Australia based on equality and mutual benefit, he added.
</P>
<P>
Fu noted that the current international situation has changed
fundamentally, and multi-polarization is an irreversible trend.
While peace and development prevail in much of the world today,
hegemonism and power politics still exist, which bring instability.
</P>
<P>
He said that a new security concept characterized by mutual
trust, mutual benefit, equality and cooperation should be
developed.
</P>
</TEXT>
