will be in India from April 23 to 27, said a spokesman of the
ministry, Jean-Francois Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Bureau said relations between France and India have been
strengthened considerably over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
Indian President K.R. Narayanan made a state visit to France
this week, during which he discussed with French President Jacques
Chirac bilateral ties and cooperation in political, economic and
cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also expressed identical views on the necessity
for a multipolar world structure.
</P>
<P>
Chirac initiated during his visit to India in 1998 a "strategic
dialogue" between the two countries to consult each other on
global and regional security issues.
</P>
<P>
France has also urged India to sign the Comprehensive Test Ban
Treaty after India and Pakistan conducted nuclear tests in 1998.
</P>
</TEXT>
