<TEXT>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) picked up 21.36 points
to close at 2,080.27 in thin trading.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume contracted to 186.06 million shares
worth 478.92 million Singapore dollars (about 282.28 million U.S.
dollars). There were 122 gainers against 179 with 230 remaining
flat.
</P>
<P>
St Engg topped the volume list with a turnover of 22.49 million
units. it was followed by DBS Land which had 7.76 million shares
done. NOL was the next with 7.49 million shares changing hands.
</P>
