<HEADLINE> Donation from Belgium for Handicapped Children in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The government of Belgium today
signed a memorandum on cooperation and donation with a
rehabilitation center for disabled children in this capital of
northeast China's Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian government will provide 200,000 to 300,000 yuan for
a three-year personnel training program of the Liaoning
Rehabilitation Center for Disabled Children, according to the
memorandum.
</P>
<P>
According to the program, four professionals from the China
Disabled Persons' Federation (CDPF), Liaoning Disabled Persons'
Federation and the center will receive medical training for
rehabilitation in Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Wivina Demeester, representative of the Belgian government,
said that Belgium has donated 43 sets of medical equipment valued
at five million yuan to the center since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Up to date, the government has trained eight managers and
technicians for the center, she said, the medical equipment has
been used for rehabilitation for more than 90,000 disabled persons.
</P>
<P>
Presently, there are 1.6 million disabled people in Liaoning,
accounting for 3.9 percent of the province's population.  
</P>
