<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Two Giant Groups in Telecom Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- After more than two years of
deliberation and preparations, the China Telecommunications (Group)
Co. and the China Mobile Telecommunications (Group) Co. jointly
announced their establishment here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the inaugural meeting today, Minister of
Information Industry Wu Jichuan said that the establishment of the
two groups marks the strategic restructuring and a new
breakthrough in China's telecommunications industry.
</P>
<P>
"This is a big event in the history of China's
telecommunications development, it will surely play an active role
in accelerating telecommunications development, promoting an
information-oriented national economy and raising the
competitiveness of China's information industry in the
international market," he said.
</P>
<P>
The registered capital of China Telecommunications (Group) Co.
and the China Mobile Telecommunications (Group) Co. is 220 billion
yuan and 51.8 billion yuan, respectively, both ranking among the
country's State-owned extra-large companies.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the leadership of the two companies has been
ratified by the State Council.
</P>
<P>
According to Wu, China's telecommunications industry has been
developing rapidly in recent years, giving a great push forward to
the country's opening up and reform drive and modernization
construction. The restructuring of the telecommunications sector
over the past few years has improved the competing and development
capability of the industry as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Last year China's telecommunications industry realized a growth
of 24.6 percent in business revenues, ranking forefront among all
industries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two companies will operate independently. The
Ministry of Information Industry will play an administrative role
to step up its macro-control and guidance functions over the whole
industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
