<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Parents of Belgian Boys to Pay for Train Crash Damages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Parents of three boys who caused
a train crash in Belgium rail line on Tuesday have to pay for part
of damages of millions of Belgian francs, local media said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Three boys, aged 8, 9 and 13 respectively, have confessed that
they had put a concrete block on a crucial switch in a hope to
watch a train crash.
</P>
<P>
The train at a high speed rammed into another coming from the
opposite direction. One of the train drivers was killed and many
passengers injured in the accident.
</P>
<P>
In Belgium, a family insurance usually covers damages caused by
children, also when they do so on purpose. But the amount paid by
the insurance company is limited. Therefore, the parents need to
pay the rest.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian national railway company estimated that the damages
may run into millions of Belgian francs, not including the removal
of the wreckage, deviations and delays.
</P>
<P>
The accident happened on the line between Namur and Charleroi
in southern Belgium. By Thursday morning, the line was cleared and
traffic returned to normal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
