<HEADLINE> Zhongshan in Guangdong Attracts Overseas Investors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHONGSHAN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Zhongshan City in south China's
Guangdong Province is attracting a growing number of overseas
investors.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the city approved 57 overseas-
invested projects from January to March, with 184.54 million U.S.
dollars in contractual overseas investment, representing an annual
increase of 35.7 percent and 194.8 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, 112.8 million U.S. dollars of overseas
investment was used in Zhongshan, up 3.83 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
In the three-month period, the city reported a total foreign
trade volume of 1.28 billion U.S. dollars, up 24.5 percent year on
year. Exports accounted for 770 million U.S. dollars and imports,
510 million U.S. dollars, up 26.3 percent and 21.7 percent,
respectively. 
</P>
