<HEADLINE> Thailand, Cambodia Settle Border Row </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gen. Surayudh Chulanont, Commander in Chief of Thai Army said
Thursday that the governments of the two countries had, in
principle,settled the problems after negotiations between Thai
Foreign Minister Surin Pitsuwan and Cambodian Prime Minister Hun
Sen, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
It said that the negotiations had resulted in a practice to
remove the fill of land along a bank of the Klong Luek Canal in
the Cambodian soil.
</P>
<P>
A Cambodian casino construction project near the border has
involved the fill of land of the Klong Luek Canal bank on the
Cambodian soil, causing the bank to be five meters higher than
before, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Thai authorities have expressed concerns that the fill of land
along the bank of Klong Luek Canal in the Cambodian side could
alter the course of the canal, which is regarded as the border
line between Thailand and Cambodia, and may cause floods and other
effects on the canal bank on the Thai soil in the long run, it
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
