<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Police Say Separatist Group Prime Suspect of Bomb Attack in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 20 (Xinhua) -- French police said on Thursday that
a separatist group called "Brittany Revolutionary Army (ARB)" was
the prime suspect in a bomb attack on Wednesday against a
McDonald's restaurant in Brittany.
</P>
<P>
The attack, which took place near the Brittany city of Dinan,
killed a 27-year-old woman worker of the restaurant and triggered
widespread condemnation in France.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said that the bombing device used in the attack
was the same as those stolen in September last year by the ARB and
the Basque separatist group ETA from an ammunitions stock in
Plevin, Brittany.
</P>
<P>
French officials said that the ARB has provided the ETA with
logistical support.
</P>
<P>
Police said that a bombing device defused on Wednesday outside
a post office in Rennes, the capital of Brittany, also came from
the stolen materials.
</P>
<P>
So far no one has claimed responsibility for Wednesday's attack,
which was the first deadly one since the ARB launched its campaign
for independence of Brittany, a historically Celtic region, from
France years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
