<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Small Loans Help Chinese Farmers Escape Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Fang Jian, a poor farmer in
Shangnan county in northwest China's Shaanxi Province, is now
leading a better life thanks to a loan provided by the local
agricultural bank.
</P>
<P>
With a meager annual income of 2,500 yuan (about 300 US dollars)
for his five-member family, Fang used to have a very hard life. In
March last year, he borrowed 2,000 yuan from the county's
agricultural bank and used the money to grow mushrooms and herbs,
earning 5,000 yuan (about 600 dollars) by the year end.
</P>
<P>
Like Fang, more than two hundred of his villagers also escaped
poverty through growing cash crops with financial assistance from
the local agricultural banks.
</P>
<P>
The system of small loans was introduced to China in the mid-
1990s. Agricultural banks and branches give loans of 1,000-3,000
yuan (120-360 dollars) to poor farmers.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, 97 percent of the destitute
families in Shangluo prefecture in Shaanxi received small loans.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Power Stations To Be Built on Upper Reaches of Yellow River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China plans to build more hydro-
power stations on the upper reaches of the Yellow River in the
next few years to tap rich electric power resources in the area.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of the China National Electric Power
Company said that some of the large and medium-sized projects will
start this year.
</P>
<P>
The 918-kilometer-long section of the Yellow River between the
Longyang Gorge in Qinghai Province and Qingtong Gorge in the
Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region has a 1,324 meter drop, containing
great potential for developing electric power.
</P>
<P>
The official said that 25 large and medium-sized power stations
designated have a combined installed capacity of 15.878 million
kilowatts, generating 56.77 billion kilowatt hours of electricity
annually.
</P>
<P>
Seven power stations completed or under construction boast a
combined installed capacity of 5.618 million kilowatts. Only one-
third of the total hydropower resources in the upper reaches of
the Yellow River have been developed.
</P>
<P>
With the construction of these power projects, the hydro-power
resources in the upper reaches of the Yellow River will be fully
exploited.
</P>
<P>
The 5,400-km-long Yellow River originates in the Qinghai-Tibet
plateau in northwest China, runs through nine provinces and
autonomous regions, and flows into the Bohai Sea in east China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
