<HEADLINE> Thailand Voted Best by Tourists From 3 European  Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Swedish, Norwegian and Russian
tourists and travel agents have voted Thailand as the most popular
tourist destination in the world this year, according to a press
release of Tourism Authority of Thailand (TAT) and a report of
Thailand News Agency (TNA) on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Swedish travel agents have named Thailand the "Best Tourist
Country in the World" for the fourth year running, the TAT press
release said.
</P>
<P>
An impressive 34 percent of the travel agents surveyed for the
Travel News Grand Travel Award 2000 voted for Thailand. In the
1999 survey, Thailand was the choice of 28 percent and in 1998 the
choice of 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
Norwegian travel agents in January also voted Thailand as the
world's best tourist destination for the second consecutive year
in a similar survey commissioned by Travel News Norway, the
release said.
</P>
<P>
The four Nordic countries, namely Sweden, Denmark, Norway and
Finland, are Thailand's third largest market in Europe. Tourist
arrivals in 1999 from these countries totaled 345,437, an increase
of 19.71 percent over 1998.
</P>
<P>
A report of TNA said Thailand was also rated in a survey the
most popular destination among Russian tourists in the past one
and a half years. The survey was conducted by the Russian
Travelling Agents' Association, with 156 owners of travel agency
being interviewed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
