<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandans Use Over 60 Million Condoms Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Over 60 million condoms are used
in Uganda annually and female condom use has picked up to about
one million, the New Vision daily reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The number is expected to rise further following massive
awareness on the sexually transmitted disease preventive programs
in the country, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The secret of Uganda, a country with a population of 22
million, in fighting against AIDS is an open policy to sensitize
the public, especially the youth, on the use of contraceptives,
said John Rwomushana, head of the health and research unit at the
Uganda AIDS Commission.
</P>
<P>
The first case of AIDS was reported in Uganda in 1982. AIDS
prevalence rate was as high as over 30 percent in late 1980s and
early 1990s. Nearly two million Ugandans have been confirmed dead
as a result of the HIV/AIDS scourge ever since.
</P>
<P>
However, the national HIV/AIDS prevalence rate has dropped to
10 percent due to the government's increasing efforts against the
disease and great enhancement of the people's awareness in this
regard.
</P>
<P>
Uganda is the only African country where AIDS prevalence rate
is dropping. It aims to reduce the current infection rate from 10
percent to 7. 5 percent by the year 2005. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
