<HEADLINE> Angola Seeks Portuguese Clarification on Death of Angolans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government is seeking
for urgent explanations from the Portuguese authorities about the
reasons behind the killing of five Angolan nationals in Lisbon's
"Luanda" disco gas attack, official news agency Angop reported
here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This position came from the session of the cabinet council's
standing commission, chaired by Angolan President Jose Eduardo dos
Santos, the report said.
</P>
<P>
"The government expects that the moral and material minders of
this crime are civil and criminally held responsible," reads a
communique distributed by the standing commission.
</P>
<P>
In the communique, the government expressed "worry about the
climate of insecurity and hostility" that might arise within the
Angolan community living in Portugal, resulting from the
"inappropriate" statements uttered by some political circles and
certain media.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan government appeals to the Portuguese authorities to
take measures to guarantee the security of the Angolan citizens.
</P>
<P>
In a message of solidarity, the government expressed its most
"heartfelt condolences" to the mourning families.
</P>
<P>
Five Angolans, one spaniard and one Portuguese citizen were
killed at dawn last Sunday, when unidentified elements dropped two
toxic gas containers inside the "Luanda" disco in downtown Lisbon.
 
