<HEADLINE> Doctors Help Couples with Sexual Problems </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Shijiazhuang No. 6
Hospital in the northern China province of Hebei recently opened a
clinic specifically designed to help couples who have problems in
their sexual lives.
</P>
<P>
According to doctors, the clinic will provide psychological
counseling and medical treatment at the same time. The couples
will stay in a cozy room at the clinic, and the pink-colored
curtains will give them a sense of home.
</P>
<P>
With the aid of the couples' detailed medical histories,
doctors will be able to prescribe appropriate treatment plans for
them.
</P>
<P>
Four such clinics have been established nationwide so far.
</P>
<P>
Chinese people in the past were reluctant to talk about their
private lives with others, and unsatisfactory sexual relations
between husband and wife often resulted in anxiety, quarrels, and
even divorce.
</P>
<P>
The divorce rate in China has been rapidly increasing in the
last few years, and now stands at 10 percent of all marriages.
Sexual disharmony is considered to be one of the main reasons for
this rise. 
</P>
