<HEADLINE> Agricultural Giant Starts Spring Sowing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in Anhui Province, an
agricultural giant in east China, are now going all out in their
spring sowing.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that the sowing acreage in the province will
reach 1.5 million hectares. The growing acreage for high-
efficiency economic crops including potatoes, maize, and peanuts
will increase by wide margins; that of early rice will drop about
ten percent on a yearly basis to 340,000 hectares, but the acreage
for high-quality rice will increase.
</P>
<P>
Farmers are adding fertilizer to the soil and weeding and
killing pests, while seeds, chemical fertilizers, and pesticide
are in full supply and are being sold at stable prices. 
