<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Gem, Jewelry Exports Up 30 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the Gem and Jewelry Export Promotion Council (
GJEPC), the gem and jewelry industry thus continues to be a
leading foreign exchange earner for the country. Its share is
expected to account for 20 percent of all exports out of India.
</P>
<P>
India's share of cut and polished diamonds rose to 55 percent
in terms of value from 50 percent last year. In terms of carats
and pieces exported, India continued to enjoy a share of 80
percent and 90 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to the GJEPC, Indian exports of cut and polished
diamonds during 1999-2000 were 6.646 billion dollars against 5.026
billion dollars recorded a year ago, thus recording a 36.72
percent growth.
</P>
<P>
Gold jewelry exports too rose to 987 million dollars from 846
million dollars during the period, a growth of 20.32 percent. The
colored gemstones sector achieved a growth of 18.34 percent,
aggregating 205 million dollars against 179 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
