<HEADLINE> Zambia Arrests Envoy's Wife, Son for Ivory Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The wife and son of an African
diplomat have been arrested by Zambian authorities for illegal
possession and export of 53 pieces of ivory, Zambia Daily Mail
reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Early last week, the two managed to slip a security dragnet
after the Drug Enforcement Commission of Zambia intercepted the
contraband at Lusaka International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The two were however not so lucky last Saturday when they were
arrested by Zambia Wildlife Authority (ZWA) as they sneaked back
into the country with different diplomatic passports in the hope
of collecting the seized ivory.
</P>
<P>
The suspects' names have been withheld.
</P>
<P>
ZWA public relations officer Tennyson Msimuko said his office
is consulting Zambian foreign ministry to determine the next
course of action in view of their diplomatic status.
</P>
<P>
Sources in ZWA told Zambia Information Service that the two had
an established ivory market in Bangkok and Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
