<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices fell in Tokyo Thursday,
dampened by selling ahead of next Monday's reshuffle of the Nikkei
index's components.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange lost 127.30 points, or 0.67
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 18,959.32.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX) which covers
all First Section issues, however, rose 9.18 points, or 0.57
percent, to 1,629.00.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section went up to 692.05 million shares
from Wednesday's 681.59 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Yasuda Trust and Banking was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Investors were raising funds to buy 30 issues that will be
replacing 30 others on the Nikkei, by selling other stocks,
traders said, adding that such moves in the market will continue
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Export-oriented blue chips were generally higher, while air
transportation issues also gained on expectations that many people
will travel abroad during Japan's Golden Week holiday season from
late April to early May, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Information and telecom issues were generally lower, while
paper manufacturers, oil distributors and real estate companies
also saw large declines.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, gainers outpaced
losers 757 to 525, with 110 issues closing unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
