<HEADLINE> Shanghai Firms Contract More Projects Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai companies reported
contracting a combined 744 million US dollars worth of overseas
engineering projects last year, up 61.5 percent over the previous
year, according to the Shanghai Municipal Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
These 93 projects include a 50-million-US-dollar housing
project in Hong Kong and a 30-million-US-dollar construction
contract for a sewage treatment plant in Thailand.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Shanghai also signed 918 contracts valued at 195
million US dollars to send local labors to work abroad. 
</P>
