<HEADLINE> Seventh China-ASEAN Dialogue Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua)-- The Seventh China-ASEAN (
Association of Southeast Asia Nations) Dialogue, co-sponsored by
China Institute of Contemporary International Relations (CICIR)
and the Institute of Strategic and International Studies (ISIS) of
ASEAN, opened here today.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day event, experts from CICIR and ASEAN nations
will have an in-depth discussion on relations among major powers
in the Asia-Pacific region, regional cooperation, and the
cooperation between China and the ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
The dialogue, a regularly-held non-governmental forum, has
played a positive role in promoting mutual understanding and trust
between China and the ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
The ISIS is a research institute established by the security
and international studies organizations of the ASEAN countries.
