<HEADLINE> China Invites EU to Come Again for WTO Talks: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese trade minister Shi
Guangsheng has again invited the European Union (EU) delegation to
come again to Beijing for more talks concerning China's entry into
the World Trade Organization (WTO), Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Sun Yuxi said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said at a regular press conference that he
believes the two sides will "very soon" begin a new round of talks
on China's WTO accession.
</P>
<P>
The last round of talks between Shi Guangsheng and Pascal Lamy,
trade commissioner of the EU, held in Beijing at the end of March,
were "positive" and "fruitful," Sun said.
</P>
<P>
So far, China has completed talks on its entry into the WTO
with more than 30 members of the organization. Among the remaining
few members China has yet to reach a deal with, talks with some,
including the EU, are near final conclusion, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
