<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA Regular Season Ends on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 20 (Xinhua) -- On the last busy day of the
1999-2000 regular season, the Spurs, Hornets and Pistons all
improved their playoff positions with Charles Barkley saying
farewell to the NBA on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Despite Tim Duncan sat out with a knee injury, the Spurs
rallied from a 17-point deficit in the fourth quarter to beat the
league-leading Los Angeles Lakers 103-98 in overtime.
</P>
<P>
The Spurs took three of four this season, the only team to win
the season series from the Lakers who lost to the Spurs in the
Western Conference semifinals last season.
</P>
<P>
In Charlotte, the Hornets clinched fourth place in the East
with an 83-73 victory over the Miami Heat, their seventh straight
win.
</P>
<P>
Eddie Jones and Anthony Mason scored 14 points apiece for the
Hornets (49-33).
</P>
<P>
At Detroit, the Pistons manipulated the Chicago Bulls for a 112-
91 victory as Jerry Stackhouse scored 21 points, avoiding the
conference-leading Indiana Pacers in the first round.
</P>
<P>
In Houston, Barkley returned to the NBA for six minutes before
he walked off into retirement. He scored two points on 1-of-3
shooting, collecting one rebound and one assist as his Rockets
fell 96-92 to the Vancouver Grizzlies.
</P>
<P>
In Milwaukee, the Bucks led the whole way but Detroit's win
made their 110-105 victory over the Washington Wizards meaningless.
Milwaukee will face top-seeded Indiana in the opening round for
the second straight season.
</P>
<P>
At Minnesota, Steve Nash had 22 points, 10 assists and eight
rebounds as the Dallas Mavericks reached 40 wins for the first
time in a decade with a 113-107 victory over the playoff-bound
Timberwolves.
</P>
<P>
In Portland, Nick Van Exel's 21-footer with 1.7 seconds left
gave the Denver Nuggets a 96-95 victory over the Trail Blazers.
</P>
<P>
At Indiana, Jalen Rose scored 19 points to lead eight players
in double figures as the Eastern Conference-best Pacers posted a
111-92 victory over the Atlanta Hawks.
</P>
<P>
In Orlando, Ron Mercer scored 27 points as the Magic beat the
playoff-bound Toronto Raptors 106-100.
</P>
<P>
In Boston, the Celtics handed the third-seeded New York Knicks
a 112-85 defeat.
</P>
<P>
In Seattle, the SuperSonics squandered an eight-point lead in
the second half and lost 114-106 to the Los Angeles Clippers.
</P>
<P>
At New Jersey, the Cleveland Cavaliers scored a 111-108 victory,
delivering the Nets their 11th straight defeat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
