<HEADLINE> HSBC Branch in Xiamen Relocates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking
Corporation Limited (HSBC) relocated Wednesday its Xiamen branch
to the purchase premises in the new business district of this
coastal city in east China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
The bank spent 3.1 million US dollars purchasing office space
of approximately 1,500 square meters.
</P>
<P>
The new branch location will bring greater convenience to
customers to better support HSBC's standard of service, said Eddie
Wang, assistant general manager of HSBC China Business.
</P>
<P>
HSBC has great confidence in the China market, which will
provide both greater business opportunities and even stronger
competition when China enters the WTO, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
In 1983, HSBC was the first overseas bank to open a
representative office in Xiamen, and it was upgraded to a branch
in 1986.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, HSBC has invested more than 80 million US
dollars in acquiring offices in Beijing, Dalian, Guangzhou,
Shanghai, and several other cities in China's mainland.
</P>
<P>
The bank now has nine branches, a sub-branch, and two
representative offices in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
Xiamen now has 12 business outlets and three representative
offices opened by overseas banks, with total assets amounting to
928 million US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
