<HEADLINE> Young People to Blueprint Macao SAR via Webpages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Young people in Macao are called on
to design webpages which feature the future blueprints of the
newly-founded special administrative region (SAR) of China.
</P>
<P>
Participants can download application forms at the website of
www.acm.macauweb.com before April 29 and complete the designing of
webpages by May 26, according to sources with the Youth Committee
of the Macao Chamber of Commerce.
</P>
<P>
Webpage designers can illustrate either the overall development
of the region or the blueprints in a single sector, and they can
refer to the administrative policy delivered by the SAR's chief
executive at the end of March.
</P>
<P>
The activity is aimed at enabling young people to care more
about local affairs, for they should undertake the
responsibilities of building a bright future for the SAR, said
Tina Ho Teng Iat, deputy chairwoman of the Youth Committee.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the contest helps young people get more familiar
with the information technology, she said.
</P>
<P>
A special team comprising local scholars and web specialists
will assess the designs in early May, and outstanding designers
will be awarded prizes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
