<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at GMT0500, April 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- The U.S. trade deficit hit a new high of 29.2
billion U.S. dollars in February as Americans' demand for foreign
oil hit an all-time monthly high while sales of exports dipped,
the Commerce Department said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The deficit increased by 6.5 percent in February compared to a
deficit of 27.4 billion dollars posted in January. February's
deficit was bigger than the 28.9-billion-dollar imbalance many
analysts were forecasting. (BC-US-Trade Deficit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The Kra Canal project will help pull Thailand out of
present economic crisis and act as an impetus to the country's
economy, a long time advocate of the project said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Pakdee Tananpura, an adviser to
the Subcommittee for the Study of the Kra Canal Project under the
House Committee on Military Affairs, said the economic crisis has
jeopardized the national security of Thailand, leaving thousands
of businesses failed and 4 million people unemployed. (BC-
Thailand-Canal)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- A U.N. official said Wednesday that Brazil
lacks an effective policy to revive its export trade.
</P>
<P>
Secretary-General of the United Nations Conference on Trade and
Development (UNCTAD) Rubens Ricupero said that of the hundred
products growing rapidly in the international trade, none is
included in the Brazilian foreign sales list. (BC-Brazil-UNCTAD)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Some 29,000 Belgium agriculture companies and farms
have filed for damages from the dioxin crisis which took place in
this country last year, according to data from the Belgian
Agriculture Ministry Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The beef sector submitted the largest number with 19,000 claims.
If all reports are in line with the government rules, the total
amount to be paid out in damages will be 6.6 billion Belgian
francs (157 million U.S. dollars), one billion Belgian francs more
than expected. At the same time, the average compensation will be
230,000 Belgian francs (5,476 dollars) per company. (BC-Belgium-
Dioxin) 
</P>
