<HEADLINE> Beijing To Auction 15 Medical Research Findings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Fifteen medical research findings
will be auctioned off on May 11 at Beijing's Liangmahe Mansion as
part of the Third Beijing International High-Tech Week, an
official source said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the source, before formal auction, these research
findings will be exhibited on May 8-10 at a related High-Tech Week
trade fair.
</P>
<P>
The 15 research findings, selected from more than 200 high-tech
achievements in medical science across China, are in the areas of
chemical medicine, bio-products, traditional Chinese herbal
medicine, medical apparatuses and equipment, and health-care
products.
</P>
<P>
The auction is sponsored jointly by the Center for Medicine
Research and Development under the Ministry of Health, the Beijing
Municipal Committee for Trade Promotion, and the Jinmao
International Auction Company.
</P>
<P>
According to recent statistics, only fewer than eight percent
of the medical research findings in the country have been
transformed into products due to the lack of research findings
transfer channels. 
</P>
