<HEADLINE> Myanmar Faces Economic Hardship: Media </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 20 (Xinhua) -- "Myanmar as well as some other
nations faced and are facing economic hardship due to outside
interference and instigation," said official newspaper The New
Light of Myanmar Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Although the country is rich in land and water natural
resources, it was far from being developed during the 40 years
after regaining independence in 1948 due to internal strife, the
paper blamed in an article.
</P>
<P>
The most basic political cause of every nation is meeting the
food, clothing and shelter conditions of that nation, it said.
</P>
<P>
The article stressed that all the sovereign countries have the
right to choose the system, policy and form which benefit them,
citing the principles of the United Nations Charter and
international norms and laws which have assured the right of self-
determination.
</P>
<P>
To develop its economy, Myanmar has laid down four economic
objectives -- Development of agriculture as the base and all-round
development of other sectors of the economy as well; proper
evolution of the market-oriented economic system; development of
the economy inviting participation in terms of technical know-how
and investments from sources inside the country and abroad; and
the initiative to shape the national economy must be kept in the
hands of the state and the people. 
</P>
