West Timor, the Indonesian Foreign Ministry Wednesday issued a
statement expressing serious concern over the incident.
</P>
<P>
"The Indonesian government deeply deplores the recurrence of
the espionage activities involving Australian nationals, which
only serves to impede the normalization of bilateral relations
between Australia and Indonesia," the statement was quoted by the
Jakarta Post Thursday as saying.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that former Timorese militiaman Paul Tallo
Alberto, 25, who was apprehended by East Nusa Tenggara (West Timor)
police on April 6, admitted that he had been instructed by an
Australian named Person to engage in espionage activities.
</P>
