the peacekeeping force in East Timor.
</P>
<P>
United Nations Transitional Administration in East Timor (
UNTAET) Peacekeeping Force Commander Lt. Gen. Jaime de los Santos
publicly apologized for the spying incident after meeting with the
Indonesian Military Commander Admiral Widodo A.S. on Monday.
</P>
<P>
De los Santos has pledged to expel the Australian from East
Timor.
</P>
<P>
There are about 1,600 Australian military personnel and 300
support staff in the U.N. peacekeeping operation in East Timor.
