<HEADLINE> Romania Initiates Nationwide Tree-planting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bucharest, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Romania has decided to carry
out a nationwide afforestation campaign to improve its ecological
environment.
</P>
<P>
The government's spokesperson, Gabriela Vranceanu-Firea, said
Wednesday in a briefing that the campaign aims to reduce soil
erosion and stop frequent floods and mountain slides. It will also
provide more job opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Solid measures will be carried out by the Ministry of Water,
Forest  and
Environmental Protection to supply suitable saplings for every
local region, she said.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that almost a quarter of the land in
Romania has suffered severe soil erosion and experts consider tree
and grass planting the best way to solve the problem.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson said the government-appointed advisor Mihai
David will visit the unemployment-striken Jiu valley this weekend
and attend a ceremony to kick off the campaign in Peterila City.
</P>
<P>
Woods occupies 27 percent of the land in Romania. Illegal and
excessive deforestation occurred these years against the backdrop
of national economic reform, causing many environmental problems
in the country. 
</P>
