<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0298 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China News Digest: West on the Move (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua) -- China has adopted a strategy of
developing its vast western part, making it a key task in the
national economy this year and in coming years. Following are
major events on the western development this week:
</P>
<P>
 Greater Suppport to Western China's Education
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and the State
Council has issued a circular calling for further support and aid
to schools in China's western regions.
</P>
<P>
The success or failure of development the western regions
depends, to a large extent, on improving human resources and
qualified personnel.
</P>
<P>
The circular called on schools in relatively well-off regions
in eastern China to provide support and aid to their counterparts
in the west.
</P>
<P>
The circular also urged urban schools in western regions to
offer support and funds in helping schools in rural and poor areas.
</P>
<P>
 Protection of Cultural Relics in Western China
</P>
<P>
Provinces and autonomous regions in western China are making
coordinated effort to protect their cultural relics in the process
of developing western China.
</P>
<P>
The newly founded Shaanxi Provincial Leading Group for
Development of Western China, for example, consists of experts on
local cultural relics who are conducting archaeological
excavations before the construction of roads and railways begins.
</P>
<P>
Western China, the cradle of Chinese civilization, makes up 56.
8 percent of the country's total area. The region is rich in
cultural relics, including terra-cotta warriors and the Mausoleum
of Emperor Qin Shihuang, the first emperor of the Qin Dynasty (221-
206 B.C.) in Shaanxi, the Mogao Grottoes in Gansu, and the Dazu (
Big Foot) Rock Carvings in Sichuan, all of which are cited on the
World Cultural Heritage list.
</P>
<P>
Farmers Looking for Jobs in West China
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of farmers in east China's Jiangxi
Province are moving to the western part of China to make earnings.
</P>
<P>
For a long time, farmers would choose to work in economically-
advantaged coastal areas, but the trend has changed as China has
kicked off a national campaign to develop its western part.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that more than 30,000 Jiangxi people went to
western China in March, and 11,000 farmers were from Xingguo
County alone.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0299 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China News Digest: West on the Move (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some leading Chinese experts called for the establishment of a
fund to accelerate the development of China's western region.
</P>
<P>
Lack of funds has long been a bottleneck for economic
development in the western China.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of a fund should use both the governmental
and regional finance. Other provinces should also provide
financial aid to the best of their ability and solicit the support
and help of international organizations and foreign governments in
raising funds.
</P>
<P>
These funds will also compensate transportation and
environmental costs.
</P>
<P>
Symposium Focuses on Sending Power From West to East China
</P>
<P>
A symposium focusing on the transmission of the rich energy
resources in western China to the economically developed east was
held in Beijing from April 11 to 12.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Guobao, a vice-minister of the State Development Planning
Commission, said developing rich energy resources in the western
regions and transmitting them to the east is an inevitable choice
for China and a win-win strategy for both the western and eastern
regions.
</P>
<P>
China has potential hydropower resources of 378 million
kilowatts in installed capacity. However, 70 percent of the
resources are in the remote western regions.
</P>
<P>
Ensuring Supply of Quality Seedlings to Western China
</P>
<P>
The China State Forestry Administration has issued a circular,
urging localities to take concrete steps to provide farmers with
quality seedlings in the country's drive to turn farmland to
forest in western China.
</P>
<P>
A SFA official said that the supply of seedlings is adequate
on the whole, however, the prices of some varieties have surged
due to strong demand.
</P>
<P>
The circular asks localities in the region to strengthen market
management and firmly stop the illegal raising of seedling prices
while setting a top limit on these prices.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0300 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China News Digest: West on the Move (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's Ministry of Education will earmark 70 million yuan this
year to improve the distance-learning system in western territory,
a ministry official said today in Xi'an, the capital of northwest
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a seminar on education development in the west, the
official also noted that his ministry will take steps to stimulate
east-west cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will expand the national education and research
network, known as CERNET, to cover all higher education
institutions, major vocational schools, middle and primary schools
and schools in ethnic areas in the west.
</P>
<P>
The ministry will complete the construction, development and
upgrading of a college campus network in the west within the next
three years, and will help middle and primary schools to improve
the quality of their distance-learning education programs.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Sets Key Sectors for Foreign Investment
</P>
<P>
Southwest China's Sichuan Province will further open some key
sectors to encourage foreign investment in a move to stimulate
competition and to assist the development of west China.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Governor Zhang Zhongwei said the province will open
wider to overseas investment in areas of information technology,
tourism, environment protection, tourism and service in addition
to agriculture development, machinery and electronics, building
materials and decoration industries.
</P>
<P>
Zhang said that apart from running joint ventures and solely
foreign-funded enterprises, foreign businessmen can adopt new
approaches for investment such as share-holding, BOT,
incorporating and purchasing, franchises, and issuing bonds abroad.
</P>
<P>
 "Glory Project" to Participate in Western Development
</P>
<P>
The Glory Project, a national anti-poverty project, should be
actively involved in the development of the country's vast west, a
senior official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoguo, president of the China Glory Project Promotion
Association, noted that the western development has given the
project room to grow.
</P>
<P>
In his address to the first session of the second council of
the association, the official stressed that the project will
benefit this and future generations.
</P>
<P>
Since it was initiated in 1994 by private businesspeople, 3,508
private entrepreneurs have so far joined in the project, funding 3,
829 projects with more than 10 billion yuan of investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
