<HEADLINE> Colombia Invites Spain, Norway to Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian government and the
rebel FARC guerrillas have invited Spain and Norway to participate
in a hearing on Colombia's peace process, High Commissioner for
Peace Victor G. Ricardo said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The invitation, made by the National Dialogue and Negotiation
Board, came after a delegation of government officials and FARC
representatives consulted friendly governments during a European
trip in January.
</P>
<P>
He said that the board listed Spain and Norway as assisting
countries in the Colombian reconciliation process and eradication
of illegal cultivation.
</P>
<P>
After decades of a civil war, the Colombian government and the
Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC), the largest rebel
forces in the country, have been holding peace talks since last
October, and started public hearings on April 9.
</P>
<P>
The public hearing, in which representatives of Spain and
Norway will participate, will take place at Villa Nueva Colombia,
main seat of the peace process, in a date yet to be set, said
Ricardo.  
</P>
