<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 29,000 Belgian Firms File for Dioxin Damages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Some 29,000 Belgium agriculture
companies and farms have filed for damages from the dioxin crisis
which took place in this country last year, according to data from
the Belgian Agriculture Ministry Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The beef sector submitted the largest number with 19,000 claims.
If all reports are in line with the government rules, the total
amount to be paid out in damages will be 6.6 billion Belgian
francs (157 million U.S. dollars), one billion Belgian francs more
than expected. At the same time, the average compensation will be
230,000 Belgian francs (5,476 dollars) per company.
</P>
<P>
From last May, many chickens, eggs, pork as well as beefs and
their products were found to have been contaminated by dioxin-
related chemicals in Belgium, which caused panic over consumers'
health.
</P>
<P>
For several months, European people fear that toxic substances
would enter the food chain to damage human health. Some countries
also took steps to ban Belgium's animal and animal products, which
caused dioxin crisis and business damages.
</P>
<P>
Late last year, the Belgian government announced measures about
the compensation for damages from dioxin crisis. The deadline to
submit files for damages was March this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0314 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombia Arrests 13 People in Drug Lab </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's antidrug police raided
a big cocaine production laboratory in the northern Sierra Nevada
de Santa Marta on Wednesday, arresting 13 people.
</P>
<P>
The installations, with a potential production capacity of one
ton of drug per week and facilities to lodge up to 40 people, were
incinerated with drugs and chemicals, the police said.
</P>
<P>
The operation, also participated by members of the Office of
the District Attorney, took place on the outskirts of Sierra
Nevada de Santa Marta, the world's highest coastal mountain chain
bordering Venezuela.
</P>
<P>
According to a release from the National Police Antinarcotics
Direction, the drug dealers' complex, which spread through a large
territory, was made up of 10 wood constructions.
</P>
<P>
Police also seized an electrical plant, two electrical pumps, a
refrigerator, eight "JTL" templates, six water tanks, one boiler,
four fire arms and other elements in the laboratory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
