<HEADLINE> HK Woman Helps North China Dropout Girls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Jennifer Zhow, an Hong Kong lady,
has recently donated another 600,000 yuan (about 72,000 U.S.
dollars) to help 500 girls from poor families in Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region to complete their compulsory education.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Yongting, a girl from Wuchuan county of the region was
among the first group of the beneficial. With the money, she is
determined to attain her goal of becoming a college student.
</P>
<P>
Ms Zhow, one of the founders of the "Spring Bud Project", made
her first donation of 600,000 yuan in October 1996 to bring 675
dropout girls in the region's nine poor counties back into schools.
</P>
<P>
She also donated one million yuan for the girls in poor
families in Guangdong, Guangxi, Hunan and Sichuan. 
</P>
