<DOCNO> XIE20000420.0319 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Exports Rise 47.7 Percent in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 20 (Xinhua)-- Beijing had a total foreign trade
volume of 2.29 billion US dollars, up 29.3 percent over the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
The city's exports rose 47.7 percent to 874 million US dollars,
a rate 8.7 percentage points higher than the national average,
according to the city's commission of foreign trade and economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises exported 520 million US dollars
worth of goods during the three months, up 91.1 percent, and total
exports of foreign-funded companies account for 60 percent of the
city's total.
</P>
<P>
Exports from state industries in Beijing rose 10.2 percent to
344 million US dollars, as the state sector's percentage of the
city's total exports dropped from last year's 51 percent to 39
percent.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's exports to Asia rose 44.4 percent to 450 million US
dollars, reversing the previous declining trend.  
</P>
</TEXT>
