<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0000 GMT, April 20 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO -- The authorities of Mexico and the United States have
begun to put demarcation signs in remote areas where the border
line between both countries either does not exist or is barely
perceptible.
</P>
<P>
The initiative was proposed by Mexican Ambassador to the United
States Jesus Reyes Heroles to prevent accidental incursions by
police members from both countries, according to reports reaching
here Wednesday from El Paso (Texas).
</P>
<P>
The bilateral Water and Limits International Commission's
spokeswoman Sally Spener said that this organism started to put
three signs last week, made of reflecting material to be easily
seen in the night.
</P>
<P>
The signs, one meter high and three meter wide, mounted in
metal posts, say in English towards American territory "Limit of
the United States of America" and in Spanish "Limite de los
Estados Unidos Mexicanos" (Limit of the United States of Mexico),
according to Spener. (Mexico-US-Demarcation
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
DAMASCUS -- The Palestinian students of Damascus University
held a silent sit-in in front of the United Nations office here on
Wednesday on the occasion of the "Palestinian Captive Day."
</P>
<P>
The sit-in was called by the Palestinian Student Federation (
PSF) and the Committee on Defense of Palestinian Detainees in
Israeli Jails (CDPD).
</P>
<P>
The protesters handed over two memos, from the PSF and CDPD to
U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan, to the residing representative
of the U.N. Development Program in Damascus Tawfiq Bin Emara.
</P>
<P>
The two memos condemned the "atrocious and inhumane" treatment
practiced by the Israeli occupation authorities against
Palestinian detainees. (Syria-Palestinian Students-Sti-in)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- The 11th Conference of the Convention on
International Trade in Endangered Species CITES) decided here on
Wednesday to accord protection to some of the world's lesser-known
species like coelacanth.
</P>
<P>
Coelacanth, a "living fossil" fish and once thought to have
become extinct with the dinosaurs, was put into Appendix I of the
convention, which bans any trade in the species.
</P>
<P>
The 150-nation conference also agreed to ban trade in
Australia's dugongs, a type of sea cow, and strengthen
conservation measures for Asian box turtles and African spurred
tortoises, which are caught wild and sold into the global pet
trade. (World Conference-Living Fossil-Ban)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- The United Nations Security Council should,
apart from addressing the issue of protection of civilians in
armed conflict at hand, seek to eradicate the causes of armed
conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Security Council's open debate on protecting
civilians in armed conflict on Wednesday, Chinese Permanent
Representative to the United Nations, Wang Yingfan, said with its
primary responsibility of the maintenance of international peace
and security, the Security Council should draw upon both successes
and failures in the past so as to perform its duties in a more
effective manner, with a view to creating a favorable
international environment of peace for all regions and countries.
</P>
<P>
"The Council should focus its efforts to find solutions of the
armed conflicts. Only by creating an overall favorable and
peaceful environment and defusing at an early date the specific
conflicts and disputes, can the effective protection of civilians
be truly realized,' the Ambassador said. (UN-China-Conflict)
</P>
</TEXT>
