<HEADLINE> Ten-Year Old Science Fiction Writer in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- A ten-year old student in Yishui
County in east China's Shandong Province has written a lengthy
science fiction novel called -- "Story of Qiqi and Mimi".
</P>
<P>
Zhao Rundong is crazy about science fiction and fairy tales. He
spends most of his after school reading, especially books by the
well-known Chinese fairy tale writer Zheng Yuanjie.
</P>
<P>
Before the "Story of Qiqi and Mimi", Zhao wrote his first
science -fiction work entitled "Defeat The Despot Who Controls The
World" in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Zhao started writing "Story of Qiqi and Mimi" during his summer
vacation last year.
</P>
<P>
The novel will be printed by a local publishing house to
coincide with International Children's Day on June 1. 
</P>
