<HEADLINE> China's First Heliport for Sea Rescue to Be Built In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The heliport will cover an area of 120,000 sq. m., and have a
200-meter-long and 30-meter-wide runway. It will be able to
accommodate 10 helicopters. The first three helicopters will be
purchased by bidding internationally.
</P>
<P>
The helicopters should be able to help rescue about 20 persons
aboard and can conduct rescue missions as far as 1,000 km away.
</P>
<P>
Experts believe that the heliport, once completed, will greatly
reinforce the country's sea rescue work, especially for fishing
ships and ocean-going vessels. 
