<HEADLINE> Tianjin Enjoys Processing Trade Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin recorded a processing
import and export trade volume of 2.38 billion US dollars for the
first quarter of this year, up 33.7 percent from the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
According to custom statistics, the total volume included a 37.
57 percent rise in imports to 1.09 billion US dollars, and a 29.29
percent increase in exports to 1.29 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin's processing import and export trade volume recorded 6.
23 billion US dollars in 1997, 6.71 billion in 1998 and 8.26
billion in 1999, with a year-by-year increase of 15.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has so far approved more than 300 tax-free enterprises
and will implement a new computerized administration system for
these enterprises. 
</P>
