<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manchester United Knocked out of Champions League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Reigning champion Manchester
United was knocked out of the Champions League by Real Madrid with
a 3-2 win in a thrilling quarter-final contest at Old Trafford on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Real, held to a 0-0 draw in Madrid in the first leg, took the
lead in the 20th minute when Fernando Morientes played Michel
Salgado into a wide position and his harmless low cross was
diverted into his own net by United skipper Roy Keane.
</P>
<P>
Seven times European champions Madrid stretched their lead with
a quick break from their area in the 50th minute with Steve
McManaman feeding Raul, who ran 40 meters before curling his shot
past United keeper Raimond Van der Gouw.
</P>
<P>
A brilliant turn by captain Fernando Redondo set up a third
when he outwitted three players before laying a low ball across
the goalmouth for Raul to side-foot home three minutes later.
</P>
<P>
David Beckham score the best goal of the game in the 64th
minute when he beat three defenders before firing high into the
net.
</P>
<P>
Paul Scholes scored a late penalty after McManaman tripped
Keane on the edge of the box. But it was not enough to save United
from their first home defeat in 38 matches and a premature exit
from the competition they won in Barcelona last May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
