<HEADLINE> Bayern Munich Enters European Champions League Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, April 19 (Xinhua) -- Bayern Munich defeated Porto of
Portugal 2-1 in Munich on Wednesday evening and entered the semi-
finals of the European Champions League.
</P>
<P>
About 47000 spectators came to Olympia Stadium to watch the
game. Although Stefan Effenberg and Jens Jeremies could not take
part in the game, Michael Tarnat organized the offensive very well.
</P>
<P>
He squandered a scoring chance in the 15th minute and Brazilian
Paolo Sergio scored the opening 1-0 goal for Bayern.
</P>
<P>
Bayern Munich has led till the 90th minute, when Porto's
striker Jardel equalized, a minute before Bayern's Thomas Linke
headed a decisive goal that brought Bayern Munich into the
semifinals of the European Champions League.
</P>
<P>
The defending champion Manchester United was eliminated tonight
and Bayern Munich will meet with Real Madrid in the semi-finals.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
