<HEADLINE> 7 Killed, 29 Injured in Car Crash in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were killed and 29
others injured on Thursday in a traffic accident in southern Egypt,
security sources said.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place on the Aswan-Abu Simbel road, where a
bus, carrying 50 passengers, crashed into a truck, the sources
said, without giving the cause of the crash.
</P>
<P>
The two vehicles were damaged and the victims have been rushed
to hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Road accidents are common in Egypt, where people usually drive
cars recklessly. Figures show that about 3,000 people are killed in
accidents each year and 60,000 injured. 
</P>
