<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE) reopened its embassy
in the Iraqi capital Baghdad on Thursday, marking a full recovery
of their bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, UAE Charge D'affaires in Baghdad Ahmed Abdulla
Bin Saeed said the reopening of the embassy is "a beginning of good
and enhanced relations between the two brotherly countries to serve
their joint interests."
</P>
<P>
Addressing the reopening ceremony, Iraqi Foreign Ministry
Undersecretary Nabiel Najim hailed the UAE move a step forward to
enhance the Arab solidarity. (Iraq-UAE-Embassy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's elite Islamic Revolutionary Guards Corps (IRGC)
on Thursday dismissed the accusation that the forces would launch a
coup d'etat against the reformists, main supporters of President
Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
Issuing a statement, the IRGC said that the body which has taken
shape to safeguard the Islamic republic can never launch a coup
against its own objectives, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported. (Iran-Coup)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
KHARTOUM -- The U.S. Embassy in Khartoum resumed its function
with the arrival of Charge D'Affaires Donald Titlbom here from
Nairobi last Saturday after a two-year suspension, the Sudanese
News Agency (SNA) reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Consul Donald Mulligan will arrive here from Cairo early
next week and an administrative attache is due to arrive here from
Nairobi, capital of Kenya, soon, SNA added. (Sudan-US Embassy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- French and Egyptian archaeologists have found the
remains of a Greco-Roman fortress town built along an ancient
caravan route in the Egyptian desert, a senior antiquities official
said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The site was discovered on the ancient route linking Qaft, near
the Nile south of Cairo, and Berenice, further southeast near the
Red Sea, said Mohammed al-Saghir, director-general of the Southern
Sector of Egypt's Supreme Council of Antiquities. (Egypt-
Archaeology) 
</P>
