<HEADLINE> Five People Stabbed at High School in Ottawa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Five people were stabbed by a 15-
year-old boy shortly before noon Thursday at an Ottawa-area high
school.
</P>
<P>
Ambulances rushed to the Cairine Wilson high school to take the
victims to nearby hospital. None of the injuries was considered
life threatening.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested the teen suspect after he stabbed three boy and
a girl students along with a female staff member at the school
library.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said the boy began attacking with a kitchen knife at
around 11:30 a.m. after getting into some kind of a dispute with
other students.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred as security has been beefed up in schools
across Canada to avoid unexpectedness on the anniversary of the
deadly shootings at the U.S. Columbine High School.
</P>
<P>
On April 20, 1999, two teenage gunmen killed 12 students and a
teacher before committing suicide at the Columbine school in
Littleton, Colorado. 
</P>
