wheel parts, and the damage would be in the millions of U.S.
dollars. Some carnival-goers got off their rides just moments
before the storms hit.
</P>
<P>
Power was restored Thursday morning in the town of 13,000 about
240 kilometers south of Kansas City.
</P>
<P>
Other tornadoes touched down in Walnut, Cherryvale and Eire
counties in southeastern Kansas State.
</P>
<P>
Kansas Governor Bill Graves declared a state of disaster
emergency in the four counties Thursday. 
