<HEADLINE> Dow Index Rises While Nasdaq Composite Falling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended mixed
Thursday with the Dow Jones industrial average rising on strong
earnings reports. But the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index
fell.
</P>
<P>
At the close of session, the Dow index rose 169.09 at 10,844.05
and the Nasdaq composite fell 62.53 at 3,643.88.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were mostly higher. The Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 index rose 7.07 at 1,434.54.
</P>
<P>
The Dow rallied as American Express and J.P. Morgan reported
good earnings in the first quarter of this year. Among the 30
companies that make up the Dow industrials, 18 have reported
earnings so far and all but one have beaten expectations.
</P>
<P>
The blue chip index finished the four-day week with a gain of
538.28 points after a jolt last week. The market is closed Friday
for the Good Friday.
</P>
<P>
But the profit-taking drove the Nasdaq composite lower.
Investors continued to take some money out of technology sector to
lock in profits from the strong rebounds in the first two days of
the week.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq rose 472.28 point in total Monday and Tuesday but
fell 87.16 points Wednesday. The index gained 322.59 points, or 9.
7 percent this week after dropping 25.3 percent last week.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 6.14 at 639.41 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 11.41 at 897.64. But the Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies fell 4.39 at 481.84.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 4-to-3 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,661 up, 1,254 down and 499
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 888.08 million shares from 996.46
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
