<HEADLINE> Canada Provides Additional C$8 million in Aid to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, April 20 (Xinhua) -- Canada announced an additional 8
million Canadian dollars (about 5.4 million U.S. dollars) in food
aid to Ethiopia Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Maria Minna, Canada's Minister for International Cooperation,
said her country is concentrating its response in Ethiopia, "where
the greatest number of people are at risk."
</P>
<P>
Canada has contributed almost 16 million Canadian dollars (
about 11 million U.S. dollars) this year in urgent assistance to
the drought-stricken east African nation.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian International Development Agency (CIDA) said that
the country's support of food security in Ethiopia has come to 45
million Canadian dollars (about 30.5 million U.S. dollars) for the
past three years.
</P>
<P>
The country's food contribution to the Horn of Africa has
totalled 350 million Canadian dollars (about 237 million U.S.
dollars) in the past five years, according to CIDA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
